Note: Natural Language Arithmetic Operators Test
Process called "test_natural_language_arithmetic" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Test that the compiler and VM handle natural language arithmetic operators
    Let source_code be """
Note: Test natural language arithmetic operators
Let a (Integer) be 10
Let b (Integer) be 5
Let c (Float) be 3.5

Let sum (Integer) be a plus b
Let difference (Integer) be a minus b
Let product (Integer) be a multiplied by b
Let quotient (Integer) be a divided by b
Let remainder (Integer) be a modulo b
Let power (Integer) be a power of b

Let float_sum (Float) be c plus a
Let float_product (Float) be c multiplied by a

Display "Arithmetic Results:"
Display "  Sum: " plus sum
Display "  Difference: " plus difference
Display "  Product: " plus product
Display "  Quotient: " plus quotient
Display "  Remainder: " plus remainder
Display "  Power: " plus power
Display "  Float Sum: " plus float_sum
Display "  Float Product: " plus float_product
"""
    
    Let result be compile_and_run with source as source_code
    
    If not result.success:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false and "error" as "Natural language arithmetic test failed: " plus result.error
    
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true

Note: Natural Language Comparison Operators Test
Process called "test_natural_language_comparison" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Test that the compiler and VM handle natural language comparison operators
    Let source_code be """
Note: Test natural language comparison operators
Let x (Integer) be 15
Let y (Integer) be 10
Let z (Integer) be 15

Let greater_than (Boolean) be x is greater than y
Let less_than (Boolean) be y is less than x
Let equal_to (Boolean) be x is equal to z
Let not_equal (Boolean) be x is not equal to y
Let greater_equal (Boolean) be x is greater than or equal to z
Let less_equal (Boolean) be y is less than or equal to x

Display "Comparison Results:"
Display "  Greater than: " plus greater_than
Display "  Less than: " plus less_than
Display "  Equal to: " plus equal_to
Display "  Not equal: " plus not_equal
Display "  Greater or equal: " plus greater_equal
Display "  Less or equal: " plus less_equal
"""
    
    Let result be compile_and_run with source as source_code
    
    If not result.success:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false and "error" as "Natural language comparison test failed: " plus result.error
    
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true

Note: Natural Language Logic Operators Test
Process called "test_natural_language_logic" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Test that the compiler and VM handle natural language logic operators
    Let source_code be """
Note: Test natural language logic operators
Let p (Boolean) be true
Let q (Boolean) be false
Let r (Boolean) be true

Let and_result (Boolean) be p logical and r
Let or_result (Boolean) be p logical or q
Let not_result (Boolean) be logical not q
Let complex_logic (Boolean) be (p logical and r) logical or (logical not q)

Display "Logic Results:"
Display "  AND: " plus and_result
Display "  OR: " plus or_result
Display "  NOT: " plus not_result
Display "  Complex: " plus complex_logic
"""
    
    Let result be compile_and_run with source as source_code
    
    If not result.success:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false and "error" as "Natural language logic test failed: " plus result.error
    
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true

Note: Natural Language Bitwise Operators Test
Process called "test_natural_language_bitwise" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Test that the compiler and VM handle natural language bitwise operators
    Let source_code be """
Note: Test natural language bitwise operators
Let a (Integer) be 12  Note: 1100 in binary
Let b (Integer) be 6   Note: 0110 in binary

Let and_result (Integer) be a bitwise and b
Let or_result (Integer) be a bitwise or b
Let xor_result (Integer) be a bitwise xor b
Let not_result (Integer) be bitwise not a
Let shift_left (Integer) be a shifted left by 2
Let shift_right (Integer) be a shifted right by 1

Display "Bitwise Results:"
Display "  AND: " plus and_result
Display "  OR: " plus or_result
Display "  XOR: " plus xor_result
Display "  NOT: " plus not_result
Display "  Shift Left: " plus shift_left
Display "  Shift Right: " plus shift_right
"""
    
    Let result be compile_and_run with source as source_code
    
    If not result.success:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false and "error" as "Natural language bitwise test failed: " plus result.error
    
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true

Note: Type Coercion Test
Process called "test_type_coercion" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Test that the compiler and VM handle type coercion between Integer and Float
    Let source_code be """
Note: Test type coercion between Integer and Float
Let int_val (Integer) be 10
Let float_val (Float) be 3.5

Let int_plus_float (Float) be int_val plus float_val
Let float_plus_int (Float) be float_val plus int_val
Let int_mult_float (Float) be int_val multiplied by float_val
Let float_mult_int (Float) be float_val multiplied by int_val

Let int_compare_float (Boolean) be int_val is greater than float_val
Let float_compare_int (Boolean) be float_val is less than int_val

Display "Type Coercion Results:"
Display "  Int + Float: " plus int_plus_float
Display "  Float + Int: " plus float_plus_int
Display "  Int * Float: " plus int_mult_float
Display "  Float * Int: " plus float_mult_int
Display "  Int > Float: " plus int_compare_float
Display "  Float < Int: " plus float_compare_int
"""
    
    Let result be compile_and_run with source as source_code
    
    If not result.success:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false and "error" as "Type coercion test failed: " plus result.error
    
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true

Note: Complex Expressions Test
Process called "test_complex_expressions" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Test complex expressions combining multiple natural language operators
    Let source_code be """
Note: Test complex expressions with natural language operators
Let base_salary (Integer) be 50000
Let bonus_percentage (Float) be 0.15
Let tax_rate (Float) be 0.25
Let years_experience (Integer) be 5

Let bonus_amount (Float) be base_salary multiplied by bonus_percentage
Let total_compensation (Float) be base_salary plus bonus_amount
Let tax_amount (Float) be total_compensation multiplied by tax_rate
Let net_compensation (Float) be total_compensation minus tax_amount

Let is_senior (Boolean) be years_experience is greater than 3
Let high_earner (Boolean) be total_compensation is greater than 60000
Let should_negotiate (Boolean) be is_senior logical and (not high_earner)

Display "Complex Expression Results:"
Display "  Base Salary: " plus base_salary
Display "  Bonus Amount: " plus bonus_amount
Display "  Total Compensation: " plus total_compensation
Display "  Tax Amount: " plus tax_amount
Display "  Net Compensation: " plus net_compensation
Display "  Is Senior: " plus is_senior
Display "  High Earner: " plus high_earner
Display "  Should Negotiate: " plus should_negotiate
"""
    
    Let result be compile_and_run with source as source_code
    
    If not result.success:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false and "error" as "Complex expressions test failed: " plus result.error
    
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true

